	abstract = {Alpha- and Electron capture (EC) decay properties of 257 Rf were investigated by measuring {\$} {$\backslash$}alpha{\$}- {\$} {$\backslash$}gamma{\$}coincidences and correlations between conversion electrons (CE) emitted during the process of EC decay of 257Rf and {\$} {$\backslash$}alpha{\$}decays of the daughter isotope 257Lr. So far, previously unobserved {\$} {$\backslash$}alpha{\$}(8296 keV)- {\$} {$\backslash$}gamma{\$}(557 keV) coincidences were measured and interpreted as decays of 257mRf ( {\$} 11/2\^{}{\{}-{\}}{$[$}725{$]$}{\$}into the {\$} 7/2\^{}{\{}-{\}}{$[$}743{$]$}{\$}level in 253No. A search of delayed coincidences between {\$} {$\backslash$}alpha{\$}particles and signals at {\$} E {$\backslash$}le 1000{\$}keV, which are interpreted as being due to CE emission, revealed a clear correlation between CE and {\$} {$\backslash$}alpha{\$}particles from the decay of 257Lr, which is regarded as a direct proof of the EC decay of 257gRf and 257mRf.},
